         <abstract>
            <p>The Earnings Relative research study is intended to expand upon the existing literature on the subject of "filtering" techniques or from given group of common stocks those most likely to reward further study. Some previous researchers have attempted to relate earnings per share to the earnings on a standard portfolio. The approach described in this article, however, relates a company's current earnings to its historical record. Test results indicate an inverse relationship between the magnitude of the earnings relative value and subsequent price performance.</p>
          </abstract>
